**Week 2 Internship 

During the second week of my internship, I further developed my technical knowledge by learning the fundamentals of **C# Windows Forms Application development**. I was introduced to the structure of Windows-based applications and how graphical user interfaces are designed and implemented using the C# programming language. This learning experience helped me understand how desktop applications function and how different components interact within the system.

In addition, I studied the workflow of the **Visitor Management System (VMS)** used by the organization. I learned how the system processes applicant information and how the different modules operate within the enrollment process. Understanding the system flow provided me with better insight into how data is handled and managed throughout the system.

Furthermore, I reviewed essential **networking concepts**, including **IP addressing, HTTP, and DHCP**. These topics helped me understand how devices communicate within a network environment, how data is transmitted through network protocols, and how devices obtain network configurations automatically.

Overall, the second week of my internship enhanced my understanding of **desktop application development, system workflows, and basic networking concepts**, which are essential for supporting system operations and development tasks.
